2. nap#-lu-us-ki taš-mu-u₂ qi₂-bit-ki nu-u₂-ra
#tr.en: Your seeing (is) acceptance, your command light.

3. re-min₄-ni-ma {d}iš-tar qi₂-bi-i na-ha-ši
#tr.en: Have mercy on me, O Ishtar, command my prosperity.

4. ki-niš nap#-li-si-in-ni-ma le-qe₂-e un-ni-ni-ia
#tr.en: Look upon me in earnest and accept my prayers.

5. er-de us-ki iš-di-hu li-ku#-na
#tr.en: I have pursued your course; let prosperity remain with me.
#note: The translation is indebted to CAD U/W, 283.

6. ser₃-da-a-ki a-hu-zu lu-be₂-el ṭu-ub lib₃#-[bi]
#tr.en: I have seized your carrying pole; let me lay claim to goodness of he[art]. 

7. u₂-bil ab-ša₂-na-ki pa-ša₂-ha šuk-[ni]
#tr.en: I have carried your yoke; implem[ent] the releasing (of anger).

8. u₂-qe₂-ʾ reš-ki li-ši-ra sa-li-mu#
#tr.en: I have waited on you; let peace come to me straight away.

9. aṣ-ṣur ša₂-ru-ra-ki lu-u₂ taš-mu-u₂ u₃ ma-ga-ru
#tr.en: I have kept watch of your radiance; may there be acceptance and consent.

10. eš-te-ʾ-u₂ nam#-ri#-ir#-ri-ki lim-mi-ru zi-mu-u₂-a
#tr.en: I have sought out your splendor; may my countenance shine (with joy).

11. as-hur be-lut-ki lu-u₂ TI.LA u₃ šul-mu
#tr.en: I have turned to your sovereignty; may there be life and wholeness.

12. lu-ur-ši {d}ALAD SIG₅ ša₂ pa-ni-ki : ša₂ ar₂-ki-ki a-li-kat₃ {d}LAMA₃ lu-ur-ši
#tr.en: May I acquire a favorable protective spirit who (is) before you. May I acquire the divine guardian who follows after you.

